16/03/2003
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- Britain's Prince Charles attended a conference on the prevention of drug abuse and trafficking Friday (14 March), and praised efforts by customs officials and the National Service for Combating Organised Crime to curb drug flow into Europe. 
That same day, Bulgarian border police seized 31.5 kg of heroin at the Vidin Ferry border checkpoint with Romania. 
The customs agency estimated the value of the haul at $1.1m. 
Before leaving Sofia, Prince Charles met with Prime Minister Simeon Saxe-Coburg. 
They discussed Iraq and bilateral ties. 
(Standart - 15/03/03; BTA, Dnevnik, Novinite - 14/03/03)
